line_1: And thou thyself o'er ev'ry country sown,
line_2: With none on earth that thou canst call thine own;

line_1: The seeds of science in his blood were sown,

line_1: Nor can'st thou reap the field thou'st sown.
line_2: Hope along with Time is flown,

line_1: When in his Mind, these jarring Seeds are sown,
line_2: He'll censure all Things, but approve of none.

line_2: In the black groves of Styx alone,

line_1: And like a scatter'd seed at random sown,

line_1: Tho' in tenacious childhood sown.

line_1: Is there with partial bounty sown. —

line_1: None thought the stars were suns so widely sown,
line_2: None dreamt of other worlds, besides our own.

line_1: Are virtues, tho' but thinly sown,
line_2: Not circumscrib'd to you alone;
